Sure! To write an if/then statement in C, you need to use the "if" keyword followed by a condition enclosed in parentheses. If the condition evaluates to true, the code between the curly brackets is executed. Here's an example:

if (age >= 18) {
    // Code to execute if the condition is true
}

You can also use the "else" keyword to execute a different block of code if the condition evaluates to false. Here's an example:

if (age >= 18) {
    // Code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
    // Code to execute if the condition is false
}
